The paper deals with the evolution of codes and concepts in a population of agents, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) concepts. The study also involves the interaction and communication between agents, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the ability of agents to perceive and distinguish states, which is related to the field of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the study involves the extraction of new concepts from the outputs of agents, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
